edu.cnm.deepdive.picturequest.service

Class ClarifaiTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.os.AsyncTask<File,Void,List<ClarifaiOutput<Concept>>>
      • edu.cnm.deepdive.picturequest.service.ClarifaiTask

  • public class ClarifaiTask
extends AsyncTask<File,Void,List<ClarifaiOutput<Concept>>>
    Class to make a call to the Clarifai API to create predictions off of an image, predicting what objects are contained within. This is done as an AsyncTask to avoid running on the UI thread while we wait for a request. This AsyncTask takes in a File to be converted into a List of ClarifaiOutput Concept. This is done by creating and initializing a ClarifaiClient using an API_Key then making a ClarifaiResponse request with the Image which is the File passed in. I have only used the General Model provided by Clarifai. I then take the ClarifaiResponse and only after a successful request. Get the specific date needed.
    Author:
    Brian Alexander

    • Method Detail

      • doInBackground

        protected List<ClarifaiOutput<Concept>> doInBackground(File... files)
        Override of the doInBackground. This is to make the API request off of the UI thread. Make a new ClarifaiClient with the API_Key. Then make a ClarifaiResponse request. On the file. We then only on a successful response, take the List of ClarifaiOutput Concept and run it through nested for loops, that say for each result in our predications, then give me the data of each result. WE then get just the name of the ClarifaiResponse and create a new Input setting the name to the name from the ClarifaiResponse we also set the sceneId and the playerId to what was taken in. Then we insert all of that using InputDao
